			<div class="content" id="post-content-4607642">
									

<p>Greetings skippers.</p>
<p>This here fancy new thread is the new place to propose tags!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Why&nbsp;do&nbsp;we&nbsp;have&nbsp;a&nbsp;new&nbsp;thread?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">The&nbsp;will&nbsp;of&nbsp;magnus!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>So, the old old thread was six pages and now the new thread was six pages, and it's still difficult to find older posts about tags that were denied.</p>
<p>Frankly, it drives me apeshit, and that's enough to warrant a new thread. Not much changes for the users, but it makes it significantly easier on staff.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h4><span><span style="text-decoration: underline;">How to use this thread</span></span></h4>
<p>If you would like to suggest a tag, please provide the following in a <strong>NEW POST</strong>. Replies to this post, or any other suggestion post will not be actioned, and will probably make me whinge at you.</p>
<p>Your post should have the title of:<br />
&quot;Tag Request &#8212; tag-name-goes-here&quot;</p>
<p>Please provide within the post the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>Articles proving it qualifies</li>
<li>Justification if it requires it</li>
</ul>
<p>If you would like to provide multiple suggestions, please separate them with <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">-----</span> a line divider.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Q. Okay, so what happens then?</strong><br />
A. A technical team member OS or higher will approve or dissaprove your tag. After that, they'll tag the articles you provided justification for, add the tag to the tag list on O5 command.</p>
<p><strong>Q. What if I disagree with your justification?</strong><br />
A. Post a reply to the original post, explaining your position. A followup post will be made by the approver, or myself.</p>
<p><strong>Q. What if you still deny it, after appealing?</strong><br />
A. Then thems the breaks. Sorry &gt;.&gt;</p>
<p><strong>Q. How long will the decision take?</strong><br />
A. Depends on my, and the tag team's workload.</p>
<p><strong>Q. Did you seriously copy and paste the starting post?</strong><br />
A. Yup. Tough nuggets.</p>

